PN,42907
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F429A1776708666
OL,3,CEnergy plant emerges as key part of
OL,4,Csecret government plans for UK food
OL,5,Cshortage
OL,7,FOn the outbreak of war, the Government
OL,8,Fprovided funding to reactivate the
OL,9,FEnsus bioethanol plant, which makes
OL,10,FCO2 as a by-product, in order to shore
OL,11,Fup supplies of the gas.
OL,13,FEnsus provides up to around half of
OL,14,Fthe UK's demand for CO2, meanwhile CF
OL,15,FFertilisers, which is also on
OL,16,FTeesside, provides a huge amount of
OL,17,Fthe rest.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G7/11
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,430,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42908
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F429A1776708666
OL,3,CEnergy plant emerges as key part of
OL,4,Csecret government plans for UK food
OL,5,Cshortage
OL,7,FWhen CF shut down for about six days
OL,8,Fin 2021 due to a hike in energy bills,
OL,9,Fthe government stepped in with a
OL,10,Fsubsidy because there were such fears
OL,11,Fover the impact on the food industry.
OL,13,FWhat is CO2 used for?
OL,15,FCO2 is used in meat and poultry
OL,16,Fproduction as a tool for stunning
OL,17,Fanimals for a more "humane" slaughter
OL,18,Fand for keeping food fresh in transit
OL,19,Fby preventing microbial growth.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G8/11
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,430,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42909
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F429A1776708666
OL,3,CEnergy plant emerges as key part of
OL,4,Csecret government plans for UK food
OL,5,Cshortage
OL,7,FIt is widely used by the food and
OL,8,Fdrink industry as it can be
OL,9,Ftransported safely and does not affect
OL,10,Fthe flavour or texture of the food it
OL,11,Fis protecting.
OL,13,FMost visibly, CO2 makes carbonated
OL,14,Fdrinks - from cola to beer - fizzy,
OL,15,Fbut it is also a vital component in
OL,16,Fbags of salad, which typically contain
OL,17,Fa high amount of CO2 (15%) that
OL,18,Fprevents the leaves from browning too
OL,19,Fquickly.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G9/11
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,430,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42910
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F429A1776708666
OL,3,CEnergy plant emerges as key part of
OL,4,Csecret government plans for UK food
OL,5,Cshortage
OL,7,FOutside the food industry, CO2 has
OL,8,Fother critical uses.
OL,10,FIt plays an integral part in MRI
OL,11,Fscanning, where it is used to induce
OL,12,Fhypercapnia, which increases blood
OL,13,Fflow to allow clinicians to map brain
OL,14,Fvascular health. The nuclear power
OL,15,Findustry also relies heavily on the
OL,16,Fgas.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}       G10/11
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
